added.title: Tall Titan Tales
added.description: Robin tries to tell some tall tales but the other Titans give their own fractured versions instead.

added.title: I Used to Be a Peoples
added.description: Robin feels the other Titans are spending too much time together so he encourages them to spend some time alone.

added.title: The Metric System vs. Freedom
added.description: Robin teaches the other Titans about the difference between the Imperial System and the Metric System.

added.title: The Chaff
added.description: In an effort to get Teen Titan Go! canceled, Control Freak shows off some deleted scenes.

added.title: Them Soviet Boys
added.description: In order to quickly get through their chores and karate lessons, the Titans learn how to montage

added.title: The Parents
added.description: After accidentally bumping into each other in the grocery aisle, Nicole and her parents have it out. The Wattersons discover why Nicole and her parents haven't been on speaking terms for so long. The kids decide to bring about a reunion, in order to secure that backlog of birthday and holiday presents...

added.title: The Founder
added.description: When Nicole decides to pay the cable bill in person at Chanax, she leaves specific instructions for Richard to stay in the car. However he's far too tempted by the vending machine in the foyer to follow her advice. Chanax believes Richard is their mysterious founder and follow his every whim, leading to their inevitable demise.

added.title: The Schooling
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are at the convenience store considering playing truant. Larry warns them that if they don't take their education seriously they'll end up like him. To prove his point, Larry lets Gumball and Darwin work some of his many roles to make them appreciate the value of a good education.

added.title: The Intelligence
added.description: Gumball and Darwin argue with the Internet and make him mad. So mad in fact that he seeks to wipe out humanity and, while doing so, malfunctions! The whole of Elmore is plunged into a time before technology. It's actually pretty nice. Will Gumball and Darwin decide to leave the internet unplugged?

added.title: The Potion
added.description: Gumball and Darwin learn that Hector is not so happy being giant-sized. So they decide to help him by creating a potion that will shrink him down to the size of an average person. However creating a magic potion is not as easy as it sounds, and the results can go spectacularly wrong...

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Craig and his friends desperately want a Snow Day, so they turn to the most powerful people they know... The Witches of the Creek!

added.title: Snow Place Like Home
added.description: While taking refuge from the chilly Creek, Craig and his friends decide to hangout at his house until lunch time!

added.title: Breaking the Ice
added.description: While searching a once unreachable part of the Creek, Craig gets stranded with his longtime rival, Wildernessa!

added.title: Winter Creeklympics
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP try their luck at winning Gold in their first ever, Winter Creeklympics!

added.title: Welcome to Creek Street
added.description: Craig and his friends create their own neighborhood in the snow!

added.title: Heatwave
added.description: Apple and Onion try to spread cheer during a city-wide heatwave.

added.title: Apple's in Charge
added.description: Apple is put in charge of the Dollar Store for the very first time.

added.title: Burger's Trampoline
added.description: After learning that Burger has a trampoline, Apple and Onion pay him a visit. Burger thinks they came especially to see him and is overjoyed.

added.title: Baby Boi TP
added.description: Apple and Onion run out of toilet paper because Apple's been building a huge modern art sculpture with it. They're going to need more if Apple is to finish and Onion is to be able to resume his normal toilet activities.

added.title: Not Funny
added.description: With their 6 month friend anniversary approaching, Apple is in danger of losing his best friend.

added.title: Panda's Sneeze
added.description: Panda bears have a very adorable (and violent!) sneeze, and our Panda is no exception. When a Vine video of his very cute sneeze goes viral, Panda becomes a cute sensation, which causes Nom Nom to try to fend off of this new challenger to his throne.

added.title: The Road
added.description:
This episode takes place when the Bears are young cubs! The three bears, on their way through the desert, come upon a giant warehouse. It's like an Amazon fulfillment
center. The Bears try to make this box-filled paradise their home.

added.title: Emergency
added.description: When Grizz comes home with a live crab, he thinks it can become a pet for the brothers to share. However, after the crab pinches Ice Bear's ear and won't let go, Panda and Grizz have to get their injured brother to the hospital, and fast!

added.title: Tote Life
added.description: When a hipster grocery store clerk shames the Bears for asking for plastic grocery bags, the Bears realize that eco-friendly tote bags are their way of gaining acceptance amongst the progressive people of the Bay Area. But in their effort to gain popularity, the Bears let the culture of tote bags take over their lives.

added.title: Charlie and the Snake
added.description: Charlie is a solo guy who, like the Bears, would love to find a place for himself in the world. In an effort to do so, Charlie throws a party, but ends up going on an adventure with the unlikeliest of animals, a wild snake.

added.title: Letters to Lars
added.description: Steven writes about the latest news of Beach City.

added.title: Can't Go Back
added.description: Ronaldo spots something mysterious on the moon, and Steven goes to investigate.

added.title: A Single Pale Rose
added.description: Steven helps Pearl find her phone.

added.title: Now We're Only Falling Apart
added.description: Pearl tells a story.

added.title: What's Your Problem?
added.description: Amethyst convinces Steven to take a day off for himself.

added.title: The Creeps
added.description: Finn and Jake receive an invitation to a masquerade dinner banquet from Count Creepystein.

added.title: From Bad to Worse
added.description: A zombie epidemic strikes in Ooo and it's Princess Bubblegum's fault.

added.title: Beautopia
added.description: Susan Strong returns to tell Finn and Jake that her world is in danger!

added.title: No One Can Hear You
added.description: Where are the citizens of Ooo?

added.title: Apple Thief
added.description: Finn and Jake are feeling peckish and only one thing can satisfy their hunger: Tree Trunks' world-famous apple pie!

added.title: Caveman
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to civilize a caveman so that Benson will let him stay at the park.

added.title: That's My Television
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to help their favorite 80's sitcom star escape to the mountains.

added.title: A Bunch of Full Grown Geese
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to get rid of some geese that are causing problems at the park.

added.title: Fool Me Twice
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to win the grand prize on a Japanese game show.

added.title: Limousine Lunchtime
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to clean Maellard's limo before he gets back from vacation.

added.title: Reeking Havoc/Live & Let Dynamo
added.description: Reeking Havoc: This year, the Professor's submission for the 2nd Annual Townsville Chili Cookoff is X-tra special. But this X-tra special ingredient doesn't settle well with Townsville's tummies./Live and Let Dynamo: Dynamo is terrorizing Townsville but who's working the controls? Now, the girls have to battle their own robot while trying to discover who is trying to pit their own weapon against them.

added.title: Mo' Linguish/Oops, I Did It Again
added.description: Mo' Linguish: Mojo is sentenced to do community service for Townsville and begins teaching English at the Learning Annex. Soon everyone is speaking in circles like Mojo and the town comes to a standstill./Oops, I Did It Again: When the Professor realizes that all his successful experiments are actually just accidents, he sets out to do something brilliant on purpose!

added.title: A Made Up Story
added.description: Someone is defacing all the posters and statues of Townsville with make-up. Can the girls stop this makeover takeover or will they get the blush off?

added.title: Little Miss Interprets/Night Mayor
added.description: Little Miss Interprets: When the girls hear the Professor trying to make something out of sugar, spice and everything nice, they are sure he's trying to create new little girls./Night Mayor: The Mayor keeps having the same dream over and over again but he never sees the end. Now, it's up the girls to go into the Mayor's head and solve this mystery.

added.title: Custody Battle/City of Nutsville
added.description: Custody Battle: Mojo discovers the Rowdyruff Boys are back and is determined to show them that he is a more evil dad than Him./The City of Nutsville: The squirrels of Townsville are chirping mad! But when Bubbles loses her ability to speak a squirrel, the girls don't know how to calm the rodents down.

added.title: Witch's Crew
added.description: On Halloween Night, Morbucks summons a monster that she didn't expect.

added.title: The Gift
added.description: The girls must replace the Professor's Christmas present on Christmas Eve.

added.title: Oh, Daisy!
added.description: Buttercup is not a fan of Bubbles' newly created digital assistant.

added.title: Brain Freeze
added.description: When a mysterious new ice cream flavor takes Townsville by storm, the girls suspect there might be foul play.

added.title: Drama Bomb
added.description: The school play goes off the rails when the drama teacher interferes.

added.title: Birthday Blowout
added.description: Puppycorn's birthday wish is stolen by Master Frown, the biggest downer in the kingdom! To recover it, Unikitty and Puppycorn will have to venture into the most depressing land ever, Frown Town! Will they manage to recover the birthday wish from Frown before his wish (and all wishes) are wished away forever?

added.title: Lab Cat
added.description: Dr. Fox's robot helpers go on strike, so Unikitty and Puppycorn volunteer to be her lab rats, er, research assistants in a bold new experiment rocketing them into space! But as the mission grows more dangerous, Dr. Fox is forced to choose between the scientific breakthrough of her dreams and ever seeing her friends again!

added.title: The Zone
added.description: Unikitty keeps losing at video games to her little brother Puppycorn, so she acquires a super-powered video game controller from Dr. Fox to help. To her surprise, it actually controls other people, and the castle goes into lockdown like a real-world video game! At first it seems fun, but will she learn that life isn't a game?

added.title: Too Many Unikittys
added.description: Unikitty comes to the conclusion that everyone would be a lot happier if they would just think the way she does, and with Dr. Fox's help, maybe they can! Unikitty copies her brainwaves into all her friends and turns them Unikitty-fied, so everyone can always be positive! But soon Unikitty quickly realizes there can be too much of a good Princess!

added.title: Film Fest
added.description: It's opening night at the Unikingdom Film Festival! Everyone's excited to see what the friends made, particularly Richard, who considers himself the ultimate film expert and can't wait to blow everyone else's films out of the water with his own. But after playing the critic, will Rick's film be a masterpiece or a flop?

added.title: Capture the Flag
added.description: Water balloon fights, warring factions and the risk of jail time, everything is on the line when Clarence and friends play the biggest game of capture the flag yet! Everyone wants to take home the crown, and the power to control the neighborhood's juice boxes.

added.title: Cloris
added.description: When Clarence befriends an aging woman at the local retirement home, he's determined to remind her of her old self in order to convert the grumpy granny to his fun loving ways.

added.title: Fishing Trip
added.description: Mel learns that Chad has never taken Clarence fishing, a tradition he sees as a rite of passage, and decides to remedy this with a bonding trip for all the boys! Split into two groups, Mel and Clarence learn a bit about each other while Chad struggles with the ins and outs of fishing.

added.title: Belson's Backpack
added.description: After an accidental backpack swap, Clarence discovers that Belson is hiding an artistic side and attempts to foster Belson's creativity.

added.title: Motel
added.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

added.title: Inventor Mentor
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to Italy to help a young girl who wants to be a great inventor.

added.title: Jerky Jasper
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to great lengths to meet Pizza Steve's imaginary friend.

added.title: Dinosaur Day
added.description: Pizza Steve's jealousy ruins Uncle Grandpa's Dinosaur Day celebration for Mr. Gus.

added.title: G'day Mornin'
added.description: Uncle grandpa goes to Australia where he must stop an out-of-control collecting kangaroo before he destroys the Earth.

added.title: Fear of Flying
added.description: Uncle grandpa helps a young boy overcome his fear of flying.
